oai_dc:dc.dc:title: A Method For Removing Brains From Ruminant Heads at Field Necropsies
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Jenson, Rue
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: field necropsy
brain removal
instruments
CNS
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Steps taken in this procedure have the purpose of adequately exposing the brain, and removing it without damage, for futher examination. The procedure can be efficiently applied with only a few instruments, and can be accomplished in a field necropsy in less than 15 minutes.
